parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause fuel to leak onto the engine and surrounding components, creating a significant risk of fire and explosion. Additionally, fuel vapors can be inhaled by the rider, posing a health risk.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel pump

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel pump can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to fuel landing on the rider during transit, creating a hazardous riding condition.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the front left side of the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, which can result in running out of fuel while riding, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: fuel gauge shows full all the time

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Fuel Tank Threads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the fuel tank threads can cause fuel to spill onto the rider or the road, creating a hazardous riding condition.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the threads on the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked throttle control cable connections can cause the throttles to return to idle without any ability to accelerate, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: throttles return to idle without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel flange can cause a complete loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the rear wheel flange
loss of rear wheel brake function
vibration or wobbling of the rear wheel
